Problem:
class WeatherSystem {
  int temperature;
  boolean isRaining;
  boolean isSunny;

  WeatherSystem(int temp) {
    temperature = temp;
    isRaining = false;
    isSunny = temperature > 20;
  }

  void startRain(){
    isRaining = true;
    isSunny = false;
  }

  void stopRain(){
    isRaining = false;
    isSunny = temperature > 20;
  }

  void increaseTemperature(int increment){
    temperature += increment;
    isSunny = temperature > 20;
  }

  void decreaseTemperature(int decrement){
    temperature -= decrement;
    isSunny = temperature > 20;
  }

}",

If the temperature increases, will it necessarily be sunny?
